Load Recipient Lists
====================

Target address fields, `to`, `cc`, and `bcc` support a list ofentries. Any entry can also point to a configuration file in avariety of common formats that will be merged into the parent list.


to: mailinglist.yaml
cc:
  - another_list.toml
  - jsonIsFine.json
  - cuelist.cue
bcc:
  - name: Named Entry
    email: test@test.com
    title: Mr.
    first_name: First

Each entry is a map, regardless of how it was loaded. Any value ofthe map is accessible to the template engine through the context.


Greeting <no value> <no value>,

I am writing, because ...


Footer
------

You may unsubscribe here.

The CAN-SPAM act became law on Jan. 1, 2004. It says there manythings you must do as a commercial email-er. Highlights arebasically don't be deceptive, and that you **MUST** include aphysical mailing address as well as a working unsubscribe link inthe body.



